════════════════════════════════════════════════════
FIX 1 — PARALLAX BACKGROUND NOT SHOWING ON PERSONA PAGE
════════════════════════════════════════════════════

The page is flat dark grey — the global teal gradient
and particles are not visible. Background: transparent
on :host is not enough because something inside the
component tree is setting a solid background.

Do ALL of the following steps together:

### Step 1 — Nuclear transparent on :host

In persona.component.scss:

:host {
  display: block;
  background: transparent !important;
  background-color: transparent !important;
  min-height: 100vh;
  position: relative;
  z-index: 10;
}

### Step 2 — Find and remove every solid background

Search persona.component.scss for ANY of these
and DELETE them entirely:

  background: #
  background-color: #
  background: rgb
  background: rgba(0,0,0
  background: rgba(10
  background: rgba(4
  background: rgba(6
  background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #0
  background: var(--dj-bg)

EXCEPTION — keep these (they are intentional):
  background: rgba(4, 12, 10, 0.7)  on cards/panels
  background: rgba(0, 200, 140,      on active states
  background: transparent            keep all of these

### Step 3 — Remove background from ALL wrapper divs

In persona.component.html, find the root wrapper div
(the first div inside the template) and add:

  style="background: transparent"

Also find any div with class containing:
  "workspace", "persona-page", "page-content",
  "content-wrapper", "main-content", "container"

And in SCSS set each of these to:

  background: transparent !important;

### Step 4 — Fix router outlet background

In app.component.scss or styles.scss, ensure:

  router-outlet + * {
    background: transparent !important;
  }

  /* Angular CDK overlay */
  .cdk-overlay-container {
    background: transparent;
  }

### Step 5 — Fix the page-wrapper covering background

In app.component.scss:

  .page-wrapper {
    background: transparent !important;
    /* remove any background set here */
  }

### Step 6 — Verify background component z-index

In background.component.scss:

  :host {
    position: fixed;
    inset: 0;
    z-index: 0;    /* must be 0 — below all page content */
    display: block;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .bg-gradient-layer {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    z-index: 0;
    /* gradient stays — never transparent */
    background:
      radial-gradient(
        ellipse 60% 75% at 18% 52%,
        rgba(0, 140, 100, 0.22) 0%,
        transparent 65%
      ),
      radial-gradient(
        ellipse 28% 38% at 18% 52%,
        rgba(0, 180, 120, 0.10) 0%,
        transparent 42%
      ),
      radial-gradient(
        ellipse 75% 55% at 50% 115%,
        rgba(0, 80, 60, 0.14) 0%,
        transparent 55%
      ),
      #040C0A;
  }

  .bg-canvas {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    z-index: 1;   /* canvas above gradient */
  }

### Step 7 — Add semi-transparent overlay for readability

The background showing through is good but text
needs contrast. Add this to persona.component.scss:

/* Semi-transparent overlay — allows background
   to show through while keeping text readable */
.workspace-overlay,
.persona-overlay,
[class*="workspace"],
[class*="persona-page"] {
  position: relative;

  &::before {
    content: '';
    position: fixed;
    inset: 0;
    background: rgba(4, 12, 10, 0.45);
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: -1;
  }
}

